
UC-01: User Registration
Actor: Passenger
Description: Allows a passenger to create an account in the system using personal and payment details.
Preconditions: Passenger has a smartphone or smart card.
Postconditions: Passenger account is created and ready for use.
UC-02: Login / Authentication
Actor: Passenger
Description: Enables passengers to securely log in to the system to access services.
Preconditions: Passenger has an active account.
Postconditions: Passenger is authenticated and can access the system features.
UC-03: Wallet / Bank Account Linking
Actor: Passenger
Description: Allows passengers to link their digital wallet or bank account to the system for fare payments.
Preconditions: Passenger account is active.
Postconditions: Payment method is securely linked and ready for transactions.
UC-04: Tap-to-Pay Fare
Actor: Passenger, System
Description: Passenger pays bus fare by tapping an NFC-enabled device or smart card on the fare reader.
Preconditions: Passenger has a linked payment method and sufficient balance.
Postconditions: Fare is deducted, and payment confirmation is displayed.
UC-05: Payment Confirmation Notification
Actor: Passenger, System
Description: Displays visual or audio confirmation of successful or failed payment to passenger and conductor.
Preconditions: Tap-to-pay transaction initiated.
Postconditions: Confirmation received by both passenger and conductor; system logs transaction.
UC-06: Payment Verification
Actor: Bus Conductor, System
Description: Conductor verifies the payment status of passengers before or during boarding.
Preconditions: Passenger has tapped to pay.
Postconditions: Passenger payment is validated, and boarding is allowed if payment is successful.
UC-07: View Transaction History
Actor: Passenger
Description: Passenger can view past transactions, including date, time, and fare paid.
Preconditions: Passenger is logged in.
Postconditions: Transaction history is displayed in the user interface.
UC-08: Generate Reports
Actor: Admin / Transport Authority
Description: Admin generates daily, weekly, or monthly reports on transactions, revenue, and system usage.
Preconditions: Admin is authenticated in the system.
Postconditions: Report is generated and saved or printed for analysis.
UC-09: System Monitoring
Actor: Admin / System
Description: Tracks system performance, device status, and transaction logs in real time.
Preconditions: System and backend are operational.
Postconditions: Admin receives alerts for failures or performance issues.
UC-10: Error Handling & Alerts
Actor: System, Admin
Description: Automatically detects failed transactions or device errors and notifies relevant actors.
Preconditions: System failure or transaction failure occurs.
Postconditions: Issue logged, alerts sent, system continues operation.
